CUre, Nymph, O cure your bleeding Victim Crys! This cruel shaft flew from your piercing Eyes, which have the Nature of A╌chil╌les Darts; They Cure as well as Kill a wounded Heart; they Cure as well as Kill a woun╌ded Heart. But if you grea╌ter Glory have to Kill, than Cure the Wounds you made, Frown on me still; I chuse the Martyr of your Love to dye, than live the Object of your Cru╌el╌ty;
〈♫〉 Hard is his Fate, who can no pi╌ty find; But harder still the Heart that's so unkind: Yet e're I dye, I'le write up╌on my Tomb, My Judge was Fair, tho Cruel was my Doom.

